      "message": "I can\u0027t remember if I\u0027ve discussed this before or not, but I\u0027ve come with an alternate way to generate INSERTs of ~arbitrary size that is resistant to SQL injections. It may also be more performant with pgx because pgx automatically prepares statements from text and re-uses them. https://godoc.org/github.com/jackc/pgx#hdr-Prepared_Statements\n\nBasically, it generates a string with a generated list of \"($1,$2),($3,$4)...\" and makes a slice of []interface{} that it then passes in as the argument to db.Exec()\nhttps://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/buildbot/+/305016/34/golden/go/ingestion_processors/sql_primary_ingester.go#272\n\nHelper to generate placeholders in strings:\nhttps://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/buildbot/+/305016/34/golden/go/sql/statements_test.go#23",
